@node Org-babel configuration
@subsection Org-babel configuration

The @uref{https://github.com/emacs-twist/org-babel, org-babel} library for Nix allows you to define Twist configurations (and sub-profiles) from a single Org file using Babel source blocks.
Refer to that library's documentation for details.

@node Using a non-stable version of GNU Emacs
@subsection Using a non-stable version of GNU Emacs

You can pass any Emacs derivation as @samp{emacsPackage}.
For example, to use the latest unstable Emacs from @uref{https://github.com/nix-community/emacs-overlay, emacs-overlay}:

@example
inputs.emacs-overlay.url = "github:nix-community/emacs-overlay";

# In makeEnv:
emacsPackage = inputs.emacs-overlay.packages.$@{system@}.emacs-unstable;
@end example

@node Using a configuration syntax other than use-package
@subsection Using a configuration syntax other than use-package

By default Twist parses @samp{use-package} declarations to discover which packages to install.
To use @uref{https://github.com/jwiegley/setup.el, setup.el} instead, pass @samp{lib.parseSetup @{@}} as @samp{initParser}:

@example
makeEnv @{
  # ...
  initParser = twist.lib.parseSetup @{@};
@}
@end example

Both @samp{lib.parseUsePackages} and @samp{lib.parseSetup} are exported from @samp{twist.lib}.

