@node Installation with home-manager
@section Installation with home-manager

The recommended way to install Twist on a user account is through the Home Manager module.
Add the module to your Home Manager configuration:

@example
inputs.twist.url = "github:emacs-twist/twist.nix";

# In home-manager modules list:
twist.homeModules.emacs-twist
@end example

The module exposes options under @samp{programs.emacs-twist}:

@multitable {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Option
@tab Type
@tab Default
@tab Description
@item @samp{enable}
@tab bool
@tab @samp{false}
@tab Enable the Emacs Twist module
@item @samp{name}
@tab string
@tab @samp{"emacs"}
@tab Name of the wrapper script in @samp{$PATH}
@item @samp{directory}
@tab string
@tab @samp{".config/emacs"}
@tab Path to @samp{user-emacs-directory} relative to @samp{$HOME}
@item @samp{config}
@tab attrset
@tab (required)
@tab The result of @samp{twist.lib.makeEnv @{ ... @}}
@item @samp{createInitFile}
@tab bool
@tab @samp{false}
@tab Write a combined @samp{init.el} into the directory
@item @samp{earlyInitFile}
@tab path
@tab @samp{null}
@tab Path to an @samp{early-init.el} to install
@item @samp{createManifestFile}
@tab bool
@tab @samp{false}
@tab Write the manifest JSON into the directory
@item @samp{manifestFileName}
@tab string
@tab @samp{"twist-manifest.json"}
@tab Filename of the manifest, relative to @samp{user-emacs-directory}
@item @samp{emacsclient.enable}
@tab bool
@tab @samp{false}
@tab Install @samp{emacsclient} alongside the wrapper
@item @samp{serviceIntegration.enable}
@tab bool
@tab @samp{false}
@tab Enable a systemd service for the Emacs daemon
@item @samp{icons.enable}
@tab bool
@tab @samp{true}
@tab Install Emacs application icons
@item @samp{desktopItem.desktopName}
@tab string
@tab @samp{"Emacs"}
@tab Long name for the desktop entry
@item @samp{desktopItem.mimeTypes}
@tab list
@tab @samp{["text/plain" "inode/directory"]}
@tab MIME types associated with the entry
@end multitable

A minimal Home Manager configuration looks like:

@example
programs.emacs-twist = @{
  enable = true;
  config = twist.lib.makeEnv @{
    inherit pkgs;
    emacsPackage = pkgs.emacs;
    lockDir = ./lock;
    initFiles = [ ./init.el ];
    registries = [ ... ];
  @};
  createInitFile = true;
  earlyInitFile = ./early-init.el;
  emacsclient.enable = true;
  serviceIntegration.enable = true;
@};
@end example

@node Normal installation (without home-manager)
@section Normal installation (without home-manager)

If you are not using Home Manager, you can add the Twist configuration derivation directly to your environment.
The result of @samp{makeEnv} is itself a derivation (a wrapper around the Emacs binary), so you can install it via @samp{nix profile install} or reference it in a @samp{nix shell}:

@example
nix build .#emacs
result/bin/emacs
@end example

@node Bubblewrap
@section Bubblewrap

On NixOS, Emacs can be sandboxed with Bubblewrap.
Refer to the NixOS documentation for details on wrapping programs.

